cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.SY. 

The paper deals with formalization and implementation of a type system for multiparty sessions, which involves programming language theory and software engineering. Therefore, cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves logical reasoning and formal methods, which makes cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with linear types, which are used for resource management, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) possible sub-categories.
